						               													<description>A game of territorial dispute set in a generic scenario of the Spanish Main. With dice rolling representing events modifying movement, and a RPS mechanic for combat using an original criptex piece. Scoring is done by set-collecting cards portraying goods and discoveries.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;(EN) From the rulebook:&amp;#10;Nuevo Mundo (New World) is a turn-based strategy game for 2 to 5 players. It is played over scenarios portraying an imaginary area of the Gulf of Mexico and the Caribbean, where each player is commanding a colonizing expedition to America, patronized by an European imperial power to gain land, wealth and discoveries. Through the settlement of key positions and the expansion of influence, players will get the imperial credit that will guarantee them the resources and favors needed to fulfill their mission. In this ambitious competition, courtesy and peace are as good as warfare and treason.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;(ES) Del reglamento:&amp;#10;Nuevo Mundo es un juego de estrategia por turnos del que participan de 2 a 5 jugadores. Se juega sobre escenarios que simulan un &amp;aacute;rea imaginaria del Golfo de M&amp;eacute;xico y el Caribe, donde cada jugador comanda una expedici&amp;oacute;n colonizadora en Am&amp;eacute;rica, patrocinada por un imperio europeo que ambiciona tierras, riquezas y descubrimientos. Mediante la construcci&amp;oacute;n de posiciones estrat&amp;eacute;gicas y la expansi&amp;oacute;n de influencia, los jugadores obtienen el cr&amp;eacute;dito imperial que les garantiza los recursos y favores necesarios para desarrollar su misi&amp;oacute;n. En esta ambiciosa competencia son tan v&amp;aacute;lidas la cortes&amp;iacute;a y la paz como la traici&amp;oacute;n y las armas.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
